{"id":418243027,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 years, 10 months","timestamp":1604877421,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"380 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/418243027/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Delete Operation for Two Strings","memory":"17.7 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def minDistance(self, word1: str, word2: str) -> int:\n        n1, n2 = len(word1), len(word2)\n        dp = [[0 for _ in range(n2 + 1)] for _ in range(n1 + 1)]\n        for j in range(1, n2 + 1):\n            dp[0][j] = j\n        for i in range(1, n1 + 1):\n            dp[i][0] = i\n        for i in range(1, n1 + 1):\n            for j in range(1, n2 + 1):\n                if word1[i-1] == word2[j-1]:\n                    dp[i][j] = min(dp[i-1][j]+1, dp[i][j-1]+1, dp[i-1][j-1])\n                else:\n                    dp[i][j] = min(dp[i-1][j]+1, dp[i][j-1]+1, dp[i-1][j-1]+2)\n        return dp[-1][-1]","compare_result":"","title_slug":"delete-operation-for-two-strings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
